==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pilot wheel
<hw>Pilot wheel</hw>. <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A wheel, usually with
radial handles projecting from the rim, for traversing the saddle of a
machine tool, esp. an automatic machine tool, by hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pilour</ent>⟦br⟧
